I looked at it when I was 44, much like you.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> However, I know the proper way to chain pets is to keep sending them after large mobs... send 3-6 pets get one kill. I have started just sending in pets, let them kill 2 or 3 low blues, and then make a new one and repeat... I assume that means I am doing something wrong... any idea what?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Other than taking down an annoying rare spawn, I see no reason to &quot;chain&quot; pets for an xp grind.<br>
<br>
Amen to your decision to take low blues (not light blues, I hope).<br>
<br>
Canabalizing pets, is similar but not equal to chain petting.  <br>
<br>
Chain petting:  sending pets in succession to a mob, in order to take down a mob you wouldn't ordinarily be able to solo, this is used for the &quot;I can do it&quot; factor, if it's going to take more than 1 pet to take a mob then yer not killing it for xp (erm solely), your killing it for satisfaction of knowing you can.<br>
<br>
Canabalizing pets:  Summon/reclaim in succession to regain mana.  This is not a feesible tactic until 49 (lvl 20 pets cost 200 mana have crap hp's, lvl 49 pets cost 200 mana have good hp's), when attempting this with the 44 pets your mana return would be negligible due to the hp difference between 44 and 49 pets.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1843<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 4:42:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=372.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hi, I r a fuggin idjit.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> mod rod 2 + SoA still is faster ;p<br>
